    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 21-SI SERIES - REASSEMBLY - RELAY TERMINAL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="1">
        <title>RELAY TERMINAL</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0801721">Figure 21</hotlnk>
            for Item numbers in parentheses.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0801721" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0801721" filename="../figg08/G0801721.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Installing Relay "R" Terminal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. "R" TERMINAL</callout1>
                <callout1>2. INSULATING WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SRE HOUSING</callout1>
                <callout1>4. "R" TERMINAL CONNECTOR</callout1>
                <callout1>5. RECTIFIER BRIDGE STUD</callout1>
                <callout1>6. INSIDE NUT/WASHER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>Connect relay "R" terminal (Item 1) (if used) to SRE housing (Item 3) and hold in place. Place inside
            insulating washer (Item 2) over "R" terminal stud (Item 1). Place relay terminal connector (Item 4) over
            stud (Item 5) on rectifier bridge and "R" terminal stud (Item 1). Be sure inside insulating washer (Item 2)
            is between connector (Item 4) and SRE housing at terminal end. Connector (Item 4) must not touch SRE
            housing. Also, be sure outside insulator is properly centered in hole so terminal stud (Item 1) cannot touch
            SRE housing. Install inside nut/washer assembly (Item 6) onto "R" terminal stud (Item 1). Tighten inside
            nut/washer assembly to 22 in-lb (2.5 N&#8226;m).
        </para>
    </svcproc>
